  abstract     = {The parity problem is a classic benchmark for the testing of the computational power of cellular automata. In the traditional formulation, the problem involves cyclic configurations of odd length, which should converge to a fixed point of all 0s or all 1s based on the initial number of 1s, without global access to the sequence. The parity problem can be solved by a local rule with neighborhood size of 9. We are interested in finding a local rule with the smallest possible neighborhood that can correctly classify each initial configuration according to its parity.}
